OK so RxDB is **disabled** (line 42-53). The app is in "server-only mode" where `db` is always `null` and `syncService` is always `null`.

This means in `useLocalTasks.ts`, the fallback path (lines 20-36) is always used:
```typescript
if (!db) {
  // Fallback to server-side fetch when RxDB is disabled
  const fetchTasks = async () => {
    try {
      setLoading(true)
      const serverTasks = await api.getTasks(projectId)
      setTasks(serverTasks as unknown as TaskDocument[])
      setLoading(false)
    } catch (err) {
      ...
    }
  }
  fetchTasks()
  return
}
```

And for `updateTask`:
```typescript
if (!db || !syncService) {
  const updatedTask = await api.updateTask(taskId, updates)
  setTasks(prev => prev.map(t => t.id === taskId ? updatedTask as unknown as TaskDocument : t))
  return
}
```

So in server-only mode, tasks are fetched directly from the API and `updateTask` makes server calls to persist changes, which means the API responses need to include the `swim_lane_` field for the UI to work correctly.

The user mentioned "still issues" after trying to move tasks, so the problem might not just be stale data—it could be that `api.updateTask` isn't properly mapping the `swim_lane_id` parameter when sending updates to the backend.

